OL,5,Cmurder
OL,7,F"Mr Reynolds was much-loved and his
OL,8,Floss in these most painful
OL,9,Fcircumstances have left a terrible
OL,10,Fvoid in the lives of his family and
OL,11,Ffriends. I want to thank Mr Reynolds'
OL,12,Floved ones for their dignity
OL,13,Fthroughout these proceedings. I hope
OL,14,Fthat the conclusion of this case will
OL,15,Fbring some small sense of comfort as
OL,16,Fthey attempt to rebuild their lives
OL,17,Fwithout him."
